303
00:15:43,362 --> 00:15:47,662
Of course after Mr. Kasuga first locked the box,

304
00:15:47,662 --> 00:15:51,562
Mr. Furuya, the AD who had come

305
00:15:51,562 --> 00:15:53,862
to pick up the box from the TV station,

306
00:15:53,862 --> 00:15:58,262
had confirmed that Mr. Takegi wasn't inside.

307
00:15:58,262 --> 00:16:00,062
Moreover, that key,

308
00:16:00,062 --> 00:16:02,762
was a special key with no spare

309
00:16:02,762 --> 00:16:05,962
that it's not easy to pry open.

310
00:16:05,962 --> 00:16:08,362
Of course it has no hidden door

311
00:16:08,362 --> 00:16:09,762
and is in this condition.

312
00:16:09,762 --> 00:16:12,362
How on earth did the perp...

313
00:16:12,362 --> 00:16:13,962
Never mind the introductory remarks,

314
00:16:13,962 --> 00:16:15,862
hurry up and out with the answer!

315
00:16:15,862 --> 00:16:18,862
Please tell us, Officer Takagi!

316
00:16:20,962 --> 00:16:22,862
More than me telling you,

317
00:16:22,862 --> 00:16:25,162
it's faster if I show you.

318
00:16:26,762 --> 00:16:29,762
This is indeed the answer!

319
00:16:33,162 --> 00:16:35,262
Conan?

320
00:16:35,262 --> 00:16:37,462
Where were you?

321
00:16:37,462 --> 00:16:39,862
I was hiding behind the box.

322
00:16:41,162 --> 00:16:43,562
I mean, where's Sera?

323
00:16:45,562 --> 00:16:46,962
Where do you think she is?

324
00:16:46,962 --> 00:16:48,662
Hey, don't tell me that...

325
00:16:48,662 --> 00:16:50,062
In the box?

326
00:16:52,662 --> 00:16:56,262
That's ridiculous! The box is locked and yet!

327
00:16:56,262 --> 00:16:57,962
Then, why don't you open it?

328
00:17:15,162 --> 00:17:16,362
No joke!

329
00:17:16,362 --> 00:17:17,762
Why?

330
00:17:19,562 --> 00:17:21,462
I used this.

331
00:17:23,462 --> 00:17:25,462
A rubber tube?

332
00:17:25,462 --> 00:17:26,862
It seems to be colored gold

333
00:17:26,862 --> 00:17:29,662
just like the padlock though.

334
00:17:29,662 --> 00:17:33,062
I had the large prop staff make it for me a while ago.

335
00:17:33,062 --> 00:17:35,462
But, how on earth?

336
00:17:35,462 --> 00:17:37,062
Yeah...

337
00:17:37,062 --> 00:17:40,362
I'll use this and show you.

338
00:17:40,362 --> 00:17:42,062
Lend me that padlock too, please.

339
00:17:42,062 --> 00:17:43,062
Yeah.

340
00:17:44,562 --> 00:17:47,162
When using the padlock,

341
00:17:47,162 --> 00:17:50,762
fit the tube onto the tip of the bar.

342
00:17:50,762 --> 00:17:54,762
Then, I forced this through the hole of the padlock.

343
00:17:55,762 --> 00:17:57,662
See, like this,

344
00:17:57,662 --> 00:18:00,362
it looks like the box is locked.

345
00:18:01,562 --> 00:18:02,762
True!

346
00:18:04,762 --> 00:18:06,362
True...

347
00:18:06,362 --> 00:18:08,662
With this all you have to do is twist the lock

348
00:18:08,662 --> 00:18:11,362
and the padlock will unlock easily.

349
00:18:11,362 --> 00:18:14,562
Moreover, the border at which the tube attached is hidden

350
00:18:14,562 --> 00:18:16,462
by the seam of the parts of the box

351
00:18:16,462 --> 00:18:19,262
where the bar of the padlock is pushed through

352
00:18:19,262 --> 00:18:20,962
and can't be seen.

353
00:18:20,962 --> 00:18:23,462
In other words, I pretended to lock the key

354
00:18:23,462 --> 00:18:24,862
using that tube,

355
00:18:24,862 --> 00:18:27,862
unlocked the padlock and went inside the box.

356
00:18:27,862 --> 00:18:31,762
Conan who was hiding behind the box pulled the tube out

357
00:18:31,762 --> 00:18:33,762
and then really locked the padlock.

358
00:18:33,762 --> 00:18:36,362
That's how it was done.

359
00:18:36,362 --> 00:18:41,462
Right. The point of this trick is the padlock.

360
00:18:41,462 --> 00:18:44,762
That is, you don't need the key to lock the box.

361
00:18:44,762 --> 00:18:48,262
Mr. Kasuga who knew the contents to begin with

362
00:18:48,262 --> 00:18:52,762
didn't need to open the box using such a trick.

363
00:18:52,762 --> 00:18:57,662
Producer Taruoka who instructs the padlock to be locked

364
00:18:57,662 --> 00:19:01,562
also didn't have the chance to use this trick.

365
00:19:01,562 --> 00:19:03,762
If so, the only person left is,

366
00:19:03,762 --> 00:19:05,362
the one who was instructed

367
00:19:05,362 --> 00:19:08,962
by Mr. Taruoka to lock the box and send it back...

368
00:19:08,962 --> 00:19:11,062
Mr. Wataru Furuya, the AD.

369
00:19:14,462 --> 00:19:16,862
I think you're the only one who could've done it?

370
00:19:20,962 --> 00:19:23,762
You probably just did it to get your reward

371
00:19:23,762 --> 00:19:24,762
for telling the champion

372
00:19:24,762 --> 00:19:26,862
